com.github.powerlibraries.io.builder

Class ByteOutBuilder

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.powerlibraries.io.builder.OutBuilder
      • com.github.powerlibraries.io.builder.ByteOutBuilder

  • public class ByteOutBuilder
extends OutBuilder
    This builder is used to create an output chain. In contrast to the normal OutBuilder this class returns custom writers and streams that allow you to directly access the underlying byte buffer that is used as a final element in the chain.
    Author:
    Manuel Hegner
    See Also:
    OutBuilder

      • compress

        public ByteOutBuilder compress()
        Description copied from class: OutBuilder
        This method will tell the builder to compress the bytes. The returned writer or stream will contain an appropriate compressor. If the defined target specifies a name with a file ending, the builder will try to use the appropriate compressor for the file extension. If there is no extension or it is unknown this simply adds a DeflaterOutputStream to the chain. If you want to add file extensions to the automatic selection see CompressorRegistry.registerWrapper(java.lang.String, com.github.powerlibraries.io.helper.InputStreamWrapper, com.github.powerlibraries.io.helper.OutputStreamWrapper).
        Overrides:
        compress in class OutBuilder
        Returns:
        this builder
